			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">AUTOFORAGE (while you sleep?):  In case anyone doesn't know, there's a way to continuously forage, too.  Here's the commands (assuming FORAGE is your ability number one in your ability section...)
<br />

<br />
/doability 1 (FORAGE)
<br />
/pause 2, /autoinventory
<br />

<br />
The pause command allows you to see what you just foraged, and can be put on the same line as the autoinventory command.  Of course the '(FORAGE)' above is NOT to be included in the command setup.  Also, the pause command is unnecessary if you don't care to see what you just foraged.
<br />

<br />
What I do, is substitute the above command for a straight forage hotkey.  That way, I never have to worry about openning up my inventory to drop in what I just foraged.
<br />

<br />
Ultimately, this can be set up using the aforementioned methods with a turbo-fire device, and you can park your ranger in a zone edge (hide if you like) and start foraging.  You'll wake up (or come home from school/work) to find quite a few stacks of foraged goodies in your inventory.  I hope this helps someone (my first post!)
<br />

<br />
Emrysyn Pendraggon
<br />
Tracker
<br />
Quellious Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
